			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: New to LDoN<a name="18338"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 1 04 11:39 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Most LDON adventures are 6 person exclusive dungeons.  You get a mission from an adventure camp, and have a time limit to get to the zone, and complete the mission.  The zones pop JUST FOR YOUR GROUP, no one esle is, or can be there.
<br />
I believe you can start LDoN adventures at level 20, but I may be wrong, never tried one with anything lower then a 45.
<br />
Points are allocated for wins only.  If you win a normal difficulty mission, at 65, you get 51 points.  If you fail to acheive the mission in the time limit, you have 30 minutes to win for less points (11 I think)  If you fail, you get zero points.
<br />
There are LDoN raids as well.
<br />
If you have never done a PoP zone, then Exp in LDoN is probaly better then any you have seen.  I would rate LDoN exp, for a 65 at least, right below BoT.  HARD LDoNs have much better exp, probably better then any Solo exp (since the AE DOT nerf), and better then exp in any zone below elementals/SolRo.
<br />
</span></td>
